Project description

This project provides Python bindings for interfacing with theZstandard compression library. A C extensionand CFFI interface are provided.

The primary goal of the project is to provide a rich interface to theunderlying C API through a Pythonic interface while not sacrificingperformance. This means exposing most of the features and flexibilityof the C API while not sacrificing usability or safety that Python provides.

The canonical home for this project ishttps://github.com/indygreg/python-zstandard.

For usage documentation, see https://python-zstandard.readthedocs.org/.
